My Vim reference Page

To keep some of the lesser-used commands handy for quick viewing


{{ Windows }}
Create new window                           <c-w> n
Split horizontally                          <c-w> s
Split vertially                             <c-w> v
Close (hide) current window                 <c-w> c
Switch windows                              <c-h> [left]
                                            <c-j> [down]
                                            <c-k> [up]
                                            <c-l> [right]


{{ Tabs }}
*Consider using tmux tabs
Open file in new tab                        :tabe {file}
Move to next tab                            gt
Move to prev tab                            gT


{{ Search and Replace }}
Replace foo with bar (confirm)              :%s/foo/bar/gc


{{ NERDTree Mappings }}
Open file, directory, bookmark              o (or <cr>)
Open in new tab                             t
Open in new split                           i
Open in new vsplit                          s
Change root to selected dir                 C
Move tree up one node                       u
Refresh (recursively)                       r
Change CWD to current dir                   cd
Change tree root to current CWD             CD
Toggle hidden files                         I
Toggle bookmarks display                    B
Zoom                                        A
Quick help                                  ?
Bookmark current node w/ <name>(optional)   :Bookmark <name>
